FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE - MALAWI: (CHIKWAWA) BOVINE, SEROTYPE PENDING, OIE
*************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Sat 19 Sep 2015
Source: OIE, WAHID weekly disease information 2015; 28(39) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=18698


Foot-and-mouth disease, Malawi
--------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 19 Sep 2015 from Dr Bernard Chimera, Director of Veterinary Services, Department of Animal Health & Livestock Development, Ministry of Agriculture and Food Security, Lilongwe, Malawi

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 30 Aug 2015
Date of confirmation of the event: 4 Sep 2015
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: November 2011
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: foot-and-mouth disease virus
Serotype: pending
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (FMD/MLW/CK/2015/1): Mthumba Dip Tank, T/A Katunga, Chikwawa, Shire Valley
Date of start of the outbreak: 30 Aug 2015
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 1500 / 2 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Cattle in a communal grazing system near a live cattle market. A total of 2 cases developed clinical signs. The affected kraal has 2 animals: a cow and a calf. There are about 65 animals in 5 kraals which are in contact with the affected one.

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 0.13 / 0 / 0 / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: The affected population is under a communal grazing system. The affected kraal has 2 animals: a cow and a calf, and both showed clinical signs. There are 5 kraals with a total of 65 animals in contact with the affected one. The affected kraal is in close proximity to a live cattle market.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; screening; disinfection/disinfestations; quarantine; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; zoning; no vaccination, no treatment of affected animals.
Measures to be applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak(s); traceability

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Central Veterinary Laboratory (National laboratory) / Cattle / ELISA 3ABC / 4 Sep 2015 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Serotype SAT2 was identified. Two outbreaks were reported in cattle, and 55 730 cattle were vaccinated in response to these outbreaks. No information is available on the vaccine that was applied. See Malawi's Annual report 2011 at http://tinyurl.com/oruvbht.

Chikwawa is a district in the Southern Region of Malawi https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chikwawa_District. A map of Malawi can be seen at http://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/malawi_map.htm.

For an interactive map showing all the outbreaks in the area, please go to http://tinyurl.com/nq99l72, click on the territory of choice and then zoom in. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3661514,8665.]
